violations.issue: Same means (delete customer records) but contradictory ends (comply with right-to-erasure requests vs preserve historical analytics)
violations.suggestion: Reconcile the ends or differentiate the means based on specific conditions or roles

violations.issue: Different means (auto-delete after 30 days vs retain for 1 year) for the same end (comply with retention policy) with incompatible outcomes
violations.suggestion: Unify the retention policy or clarify the conditions under which each means is applied

violations.issue: Different means of handling customer records (delete vs soft-delete to recycle bin) that may lead to inconsistent states
violations.suggestion: Standardize the deletion process or ensure that both means can coexist without conflict

violations.issue: Different roles have means that may conflict (Customer Support Agent can delete draft records, but Compliance Officer prevents deletion of approved records)
violations.suggestion: Ensure that the permissions and means for each role are clearly defined and do not contradict each other
